    {
      "section_id": "para_43",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "An  Act  to  provide  for  the  territorial  sea  of  Malaysia  and  for  \nconnected  matters.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_44",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "[",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_45",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "]",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_46",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "WHEREAS  the  Proclamation  of  Emergency  issued  by  the  Yang  \ndi-Pertuan Agong on  15 May 1969 under Article 150 of the Federal \nconstitution  had  been  annulled  by  both  the  Dewan  Rakyat  and \nSenate on 24 November 2011 and 20 December 2011 respectively \nand  had  ceased  to  have  effect  pursuant  to  clause  (3)  of  Article \n150  of  the  Federal  constitution;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_47",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "AND WHEREAS the Emergency (Essential Powers) Ordinance, \nNo. 7 1969 [P.U. (A) 307a/1969] was enacted and promulgated by \nthe Yang di-Pertuan Agong on 2 August 1969 for the delimitation \nof  the  territorial  waters  of  Malaysia  pursuant  to  clause  (2)  of \nArticle 150 of the Federal constitution and which came into force \non  10 August  1969;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_48",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "AND WHEREAS by virtue of clause (7) of Article 150 of the \nFederal constitution, the Emergency (Essential Powers) Ordinance, \nNo. 7 1969 will cease to have effect at the expiration of a period \nof six months beginning with the date on which the Proclamation \nof  Emergency  ceases  to  be  in  force  except  as  to  things  done  or \nomitted  to  be  done  before  the  expiration  of  that  period;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_49",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "6",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_50",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Laws  of  Malaysia",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_51",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Act  750",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_52",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "AND  WHEREAS  the  United  Nations  convention  on  the  Law \nof  the  Sea  was  done  at  Montego  Bay  on  10  December  1982;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_53",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "AND WHEREAS Malaysia deposited her instrument of ratification \non 14 October 1996 and therefore in accordance with Article 308 \nof  the  convention,  the  said  convention  entered  into  force  as  far \nas  Malaysia  is  concerned  on  14  November  1996;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_54",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "NOW,  THEREFORE,  iT  iS  enaCted  by  the  Parliament  of \nMalaysia  as  follows:",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_55",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "short  title,  commencement  and  application",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_56",
      "heading": "1.  (1)  This Act  may  be  cited  as  the  Territorial  Sea Act  2012.",
      "content": "1.  (1)  This Act  may  be  cited  as  the  Territorial  Sea Act  2012.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_57",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)  This Act  comes  into  operation  on  22  June  2012  and  shall",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_58",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "apply  throughout  Malaysia.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_59",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Interpretation",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_60",
      "heading": "2.",
      "content": "2.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_61",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "in  this Act,  unless  the  context  otherwise  requires—",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_62",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "“chart” means a nautical chart specifically designed to meet the \nneeds  of  marine  navigation,  showing  the  depth  of  water,  nature \nof the seabed, configuration and nature of the coast, dangers and \naids to navigation, in a standardized format and such chart is also \nreferred  to  as  marine  chart  or  hydrographic  chart;",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_63",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "“baselines”  means the baselines as defined under section 2 of \nthe  Baseline  of  Maritime  Zones Act  2006  [Act  660].",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_64",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "limits  of  territorial  sea",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_65",
      "heading": "3.  (1)  Subject  to  the  provisions  of  this  Act,  the  breadth  of  the \nterritorial  sea  of  Malaysia  shall  for  all  purposes  be  12  nautical \nmiles.",
      "content": "3.  (1)  Subject  to  the  provisions  of  this  Act,  the  breadth  of  the \nterritorial  sea  of  Malaysia  shall  for  all  purposes  be  12  nautical \nmiles.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_66",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)  The  baselines  from  which  the  breadth  of  that  territorial \nsea  is  to  be  measured  shall  for  all  purposes  be  those  established \nin  accordance  with  section  5  of  the  Baseline  of  Maritime  Zones \nAct  2006.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_67",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Territorial  Sea",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_68",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "7",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_69",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(3)  For the purposes of the continental Shelf Act 1966 [Act 83],  \nthe Petroleum Mining Act 1966 [Act 95], the National Land code  \n[Act 56/65] and any written law relating to land in force in Sabah \nand  Sarawak,  any  reference  to  territorial  sea  therein  shall  in \nrelation  to  any  territory  be  construed  as  a  reference  to  such  part \nof  the  sea  adjacent  to  the  coast  thereof  not  exceeding  3  nautical \nmiles  measured  from  the  low-water  line.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_70",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "sovereignty  in  respect  of  the  territorial  sea",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_71",
      "heading": "4.  The sovereignty in respect of the territorial sea, and in respect \nof  its  bed  and  subsoil,  is  vested  in  and  exercisable  by  the  Yang \ndi-Pertuan Agong  in  right  of  Malaysia.",
      "content": "4.  The sovereignty in respect of the territorial sea, and in respect \nof  its  bed  and  subsoil,  is  vested  in  and  exercisable  by  the  Yang \ndi-Pertuan Agong  in  right  of  Malaysia.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_72",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "Maps  and  charts  of  limits  of  territorial  sea",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_73",
      "heading": "5.  (1)  The Yang  di-Pertuan Agong  may,  on  the  recommendation \nof  the  Prime  Minister—",
      "content": "5.  (1)  The Yang  di-Pertuan Agong  may,  on  the  recommendation \nof  the  Prime  Minister—",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_74",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(a)  cause  to  be  prepared  and  issued  any  map,  as  he  thinks",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_75",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "fit,  relating  to  the  limits  of  the  territorial  sea;  or",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_76",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(b)  cause  to  be  prepared  and  issued  a  large-scale  chart  or \nappropriate  scale  chart  for  ascertaining  position,  as  he \nthinks  fit,  showing  the  low-water  line  along  the  coast \nand  may  cause  to  be  shown  on  such  chart  any  other \nmatter  referred  to  in  paragraph  (a).",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_77",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "(2)  Any map or chart prepared and issued under paragraph (1)(a) \nor (b) shall be published in the Gazette and, if necessary, in such \nother form as the Yang di-Pertuan Agong, on the recommendation \nof  the  Prime  Minister,  may  determine.",
      "section_number": null,
      "subsection": null,
      "page_number": null,
      "element_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "section_id": "para_78",
      "heading": "",
      "content": "references  to  territorial  waters  in  any  other  written  law,  etc.",
